Tailwindcss-fluid-type is a Tailwind CSS plugin that provides a set of utilities for creating fluid typography. It allows you to easily create responsive font sizes that scale up and down based on the viewport size.

With the tailwindcss-fluid-type plugin, you can use the `fluid` property to set the minimum and maximum font sizes, as well as the breakpoint range over which the font size should scale. The syntax for using the `fluid` property is:

```css
.text-4xl {
  @apply fluid text-4xl (min-width: 640px) (max-width: 1535px);
}
```

In this example, the `text-4xl` class sets the base font size to 2.25rem. The `fluid` property then sets the minimum font size to 2rem and the maximum font size to 3rem. The `(min-width: 640px)` and `(max-width: 1535px)` media query ranges specify the viewport sizes over which the font size should scale.

The tailwindcss-fluid-type plugin makes it easy to create responsive typography that adapts to different screen sizes, without having to write custom CSS for each breakpoint.

